      "form_guide": "",
      "comment": "Impossible to go past the bonny mare DAKOTA LEE (1), who won her second Pioneer Sprint in Alice last time. Has won 13/15 and is probably well weighted here with the claim, meeting one of her rivals from last start better at the weights. Sits close and tries and tries. The one to beat.  ATLANTIC OCEAN (4) was a winner here two back then turned in a poor run last time when safely held behind Field Of Flutes. Has a nice weight in this and worth another chance. AWASH (3) was placed in the Field Of Flutes race, running third. Goes well here and drawn to feature. Surely one of those three wins. MAXXI BON (5) raced over 2000m last time in the Alice Cup and is coming well back in trip. Will wind up late.",
